As of **2026-07-10**, a dated, non-exhaustive conventional/payment-stablecoin set on Stellar includes:
- **USDC** and **EURC** — Circle-issued native Stellar assets;
- **PYUSD** — PayPal-branded, Paxos-issued; live since 2025-09-18;
- **EURAU** — AllUnity's fully reserved euro stablecoin, live on Stellar since 2026-04-13;
- **MGUSD** — MoneyGram-branded, Bridge-issued, natively launched on Stellar on 2026-06-02.

SDF materials also document regional/legacy fiat assets such as GYEN, ZUSD, and AUDD, and a March-2026 report tracked 17 stablecoins across 9+ fiat currencies. Treat this as a changing taxonomy, not a complete registry. Classify **YLDS** separately as Figure's regulated yield-bearing face-amount-certificate product rather than silently merging it with ordinary payment stablecoins. Likewise keep fund shares/RWAs such as BENJI, USDY, and unresolved hybrid products in their correct legal/product class. No complete source supports a blanket 'no algorithmic stablecoin' claim.
